status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"cj68v","text":"Two nasal lavage samples (NLS) are collected per person in each step, one from each nostril.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1ir2","text":"Both nasal cavities are pre-washed with 2 mL of physiological NaCl solution with the use of a plastic disposable pipette to remove bacterial impurities.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ecpfv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"qul1","text":"After 5 mins of incubation, each nasal cavity is rinsed again with 2 mL physiological NaCl solution with subsequent collection of the NLS into a tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cd3op","text":"Following this step, an additional rinse is performed with 2 mL NaCl 10% (w/v) aqeous solution and collection of the NLS into a tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4oebb","text":"A final rinse is performed with 2 mL NaCl 20% (w/v) aqeous solution and collection of the NLS into a tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f0jjc","text":"Depending on downstream applications, NLS samples can be immediatelly frozen at -80 °C  until analysis or centrifuged at 10.000 x g for 5 mins at 4 °C in order to remove cellullar debri and then stored.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
